Control the size and thickness of text using CSS properties.

**Font Size:**
```css
h1 {
  font-size: 40px;
}

p {
  font-size: 16px;
}
```

**Font Size Units:**
- `px` - Pixels (absolute)
- `em` - Relative to parent font size
- `rem` - Relative to root font size
- `%` - Percentage of parent
- `vw/vh` - Viewport width/height

**Font Weight:**
```css
p {
  font-weight: normal; /* 400 */
  font-weight: bold; /* 700 */
  font-weight: 300; /* Light */
  font-weight: 900; /* Black */
}
```

**Common Values:**
- `100` - Thin
- `300` - Light
- `400` - Normal (default)
- `500` - Medium
- `700` - Bold
- `900` - Black

**Font Style:**
```css
p {
  font-style: normal;
  font-style: italic;
  font-style: oblique;
}

Control how text is aligned and add decorative effects.

**Text Alignment:**
```css
h1 {
  text-align: center;
}

p {
  text-align: justify;
}
```

**Alignment Values:**
- `left` - Align left (default)
- `right` - Align right
- `center` - Center align
- `justify` - Stretch to equal width

**Text Decoration:**
```css
a {
  text-decoration: none; /* remove underline */
}

p {
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  text-decoration: overline;
}
```

**Text Decoration Values:**
- `none` - No decoration
- `underline` - Underlined text
- `overline` - Line above text
- `line-through` - Strikethrough

**Text Transform:**
```css
h1 {
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

p {
  text-transform: lowercase;
  text-transform: capitalize;
}

Control vertical spacing between lines and horizontal spacing between characters.

**Line Height:**
```css
p {
  line-height: 1.5; /* 1.5 times font size */
  line-height: 24px; /* absolute pixels */
  line-height: 150%; /* percentage */
}
```

**Best Practices:**
- Use unitless values (1.5) for better scaling
- 1.4-1.6 is ideal for body text
- 1.2-1.4 for headings
- Improves readability

**Letter Spacing:**
```css
h1 {
  letter-spacing: 2px;
}

p {
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}
```

**Word Spacing:**
```css
p {
  word-spacing: 5px;
}
```

**Text Indent:**
```css
p {
  text-indent: 50px;
}
```

**Common Uses:**
- Line height for readability
- Letter spacing for headings
- Word spacing for emphasis
- Text indent for paragraphs

Add visual effects to text with shadows and colors.

**Text Color:**
```css
h1 {
  color: #333333;
}

p {
  color: rgb(51, 51, 51);
}
```

**Text Shadow:**
```css
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #000000;
}
```

**Shadow Syntax:**
```css
text-shadow: h-shadow v-shadow blur-radius color;
```

**Examples:**
```css
/* Simple shadow */
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px #ff0000;
}

/* Blurred shadow */
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px #000000;
}

/* Multiple shadows */
h1 {
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px red, 0 0 1em blue;
}
```

**White Space:**
```css
p {
  white-space: normal; /* default */
  white-space: nowrap; /* no line breaks */
  white-space: pre; /* preserve whitespace */
  white-space: pre-wrap; /* preserve but wrap */
}

**Direction:**
```css
p {
  direction: ltr; /* left to right */
  direction: rtl; /* right to left */
}

The font property is a shorthand for all font properties.

**Syntax:**
```css
font: font-style font-weight font-size/line-height font-family;
```

**Example:**
```cssnp {
  font: italic bold 16px/1.5 Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

**Breakdown:**
- `italic` - font-style
- `bold` - font-weight
- `16px` - font-size
- `/1.5` - line-height
- `Arial, sans-serif` - font-family

**Required Values:**
- font-size and font-family are required
- Other values are optional

**Examples:**
```css
/* Minimum required */
p {
  font: 16px Arial;
}

/* With style */
p {
  font: italic 16px Arial;
}

/* With weight */
p {
  font: bold 16px Arial;
}

/* Full specification */
p {
  font: italic bold 16px/1.5 Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

**Best Practice:**
- Use shorthand for cleaner code
- Always specify font-size and font-family
- Order matters in shorthand
